#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:2
#: 6f11ea398f4f4d8c8c76972e56edc19b
msgid "奉加PB系列"
msgstr "Phyplus PB Series"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:5
#: 7f087424d89a4f659639ff7fdbe31843
msgid "1. 简介"
msgstr "1. Introduction"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:6
#: a54a93a2c6794f199944fca6bbf1940c
msgid ""
"安信可科技针对物联网设计通用型的蓝牙模组，其功能强大、用途广泛。可以用于智能"
"灯、智能插座、智能空调等其他智能家电。同时符合BLE 5.0及SIG Mesh规范，可直接通"
"过智能手机组建Mesh网络，也可对接天猫精灵等智能音箱，适用于多种智能家居应用场"
"景。"
msgstr ""
"Ai-Thinker Technology has designed a general-purpose Bluetooth module for "
"IoT applications. It is powerful and widely applicable, and can be used in "
"smart lights, smart sockets, smart air conditioners, and other smart home "
"appliances. It also complies with BLE 5.0 and SIG Mesh specifications. A "
"Mesh network can be created directly via a smartphone, and it can also be "
"connected to smart speakers such as Tmall Genie, making it suitable for "
"various smart home application scenarios."

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:8
#: c1327fb559e746cda2478632ccef8f5f
msgid "1.1mm 间距 SMD-20 封装；6 路 PWM 输出；"
msgstr "1.1mm pitch SMD-20 package; 6-channel PWM output;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:9
#: 77363846419240aaa9137f772a185785
msgid "采用BLE 5.0 协议，支Sig Mesh，支持天猫精灵/APP语音控制。"
msgstr ""
"Uses the BLE 5.0 protocol, supports SIG Mesh, and supports Tmall Genie / APP "
"voice control;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:10
#: 2af9eec38bb14379837f575bd41d738f
msgid ""
"支持半孔焊盘和天线孔和板载天线。半孔焊盘可把天线引导主板上，天线孔可在模组上"
"直接焊接弹簧天线；"
msgstr ""
"Supports castellated pads, antenna holes, and an onboard antenna. The "
"castellated pads can route the antenna to the mainboard, while the antenna "
"hole allows a spring antenna to be soldered directly onto the module;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:11
#: bd7066659b7d47f99a419f5bcbdbbab4
msgid "亮度（占空比）调整范围 5%-100%，PWM 输出频率 1KHz；"
msgstr ""
"Brightness (duty cycle) adjustment range: 5%-100%, PWM output frequency: "
"1kHz;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:12
#: 490e7fa13aa34d21b4a537db0f512db7
msgid "支持ESP32-G蓝牙网关通讯，实现远程随时随地控制；"
msgstr ""
"Supports communication with the ESP32-G Bluetooth gateway, enabling remote "
"control anytime and anywhere;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:13
#: 2212baaca6cd4f299fe38332c012d15b
msgid "支持windows环境SDK二次开发，资料代码全部开源，支持AT指令接入天猫精灵；"
msgstr ""
"Supports secondary development with the SDK in a Windows environment. All "
"documentation and code are open source. Supports AT command access to Tmall "
"Genie;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:14
#: 46b7b997182f4522b3465a79fba9671a
msgid "支持Android/IOS APP和微信小程序控制；"
msgstr "Supports Android/iOS apps and WeChat Mini Program control;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:16
#: 074932b3db47444c848fca11bac819a4
msgid ""
"更多资料请转跳： `安信可官方docs <https://docs.ai-thinker.com/"
"blue_tooth_pb>`__"
msgstr ""
"For more information, please visit: `Ai-Thinker official docs <https://docs."
"ai-thinker.com/blue_tooth_pb>`__"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:19
#: 15b2ef31be8d45d08a4b91c1153b4dbb
msgid "2. 开发环境搭建"
msgstr "2. Setting Up the Development Environment"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:22
#: 60a69f0825f044b1b603fdf93e44e771
msgid "2.1 BLE基础知识"
msgstr "2.1 BLE Basics"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:23
#: 772a70b178e44c74b69cefe9b3037fdf
msgid ""
"Ble 协议栈中的 GAP 层负责处理设备访问模式，包括设备发现、建立连接、终止连接、"
"初始化安全管理和设备配置，所以在 ble 协议栈中有不少函数均是以 GAP 为前缀，这"
"些函数会负责以上的内容。 GAP 层总是作为下面四个钟角色之一："
msgstr ""
"The GAP layer in the BLE protocol stack is responsible for handling device "
"access modes, including device discovery, connection establishment, "
"connection termination, security management initialization, and device "
"configuration. Therefore, many functions in the BLE protocol stack are "
"prefixed with GAP, and these functions are responsible for the tasks "
"mentioned above. The GAP layer always operates as one of the following four "
"roles:"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:26
#: 3624317184764f35a7ef8fb7946bed60
msgid "Broadcaster 广播者——不可以连接的一直在广播的设备；"
msgstr ""
"Broadcaster — A device that continuously broadcasts and cannot be connected;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:27
#: 21a80dca465147dcb10cbb1e86b90ec3
msgid "Observer 观测者——可扫描广播设备，但不能发起建立连接的设备；"
msgstr ""
"Observer — A device that can scan broadcasting devices but cannot initiate a "
"connection;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:28
#: bb68faa739e14fcb930080b27ee8007d
msgid "Peripheral 从机 ——可被连接的广播设备，可以在单个链路层连接中作从机。"
msgstr ""
"Peripheral — A connectable broadcasting device that can act as a slave in a "
"single link-layer connection;"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:29
#: e57547bdffad458fa5a3808bffe08b8f
msgid "Central 主机 ——可以扫描广播设备并发起连接，在单个链路层或多链路层中"
msgstr ""
"Central — A device that can scan broadcasting devices and initiate "
"connections, in a single link-layer or multi-link-layer connection"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:30
#: b3f6bd7fb3da451c86ffe2693c316ad3
msgid "作为主机。"
msgstr "acts as a master."

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:31
#: ad236fc89f5c428ea2bf56545c913c93
msgid ""
"在典型的蓝牙低功耗系统中，从机设备广播特定的数据，以便让主机知道他是一个可以"
"连接的设备，广播内容包括设备地址以及一些额外的数据，如设备名、服务等。主机收"
"到广播数据后，会向从机发送扫描请求 ScanRequest，然后从机将特定的数据回应给主"
"机，称为扫描回应 ScanResponse。主机收到扫描回应后，便知道这是一个可以建立连接"
"的外部设备，这就是设备发现的全过程。此时，主机可以向从机发起建立连接的请求，"
"连接请求包括下面一些参数。"
msgstr ""
"In a typical Bluetooth Low Energy system, a peripheral device broadcasts "
"specific data so that the central device knows it is a connectable device. "
"The broadcast content includes the device address and some additional data, "
"such as the device name and services. After receiving the broadcast data, "
"the central device sends a ScanRequest to the peripheral device. The "
"peripheral device then responds with specific data, called a ScanResponse. "
"After receiving the scan response, the central device knows that this is an "
"external device that can establish a connection. This is the complete device "
"discovery process. At this point, the central device can initiate a "
"connection request to the peripheral device. The connection request includes "
"the following parameters:"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:32
#: 4b03f5cd59ff4845af8095a2eecefa3f
msgid ""
"连接间隔——在两个 BLE 设备的连接中使用调频机制，两个设备使用特定的信道收发数"
"据，然后过一段时间后再使用新的信道。（链路层处理信道切换），两设备在信道切换"
"后收发数据称之为连接事件，即使没有应用数据的收发，两个设备任然会通过交换链路"
"层数据来维持连接，连接间隔就是两个连接事件之间的时间间隔，连接间隔以1.25ms 为"
"单位，连接间隔的值为 6（7.5ms）~3200（4s）。"
msgstr ""
"Connection interval — In a connection between two BLE devices, a frequency-"
"hopping mechanism is used. The two devices transmit and receive data on a "
"specific channel, then switch to a new channel after a period of time. "
"(Channel switching is handled by the link layer.) The data transmission and "
"reception after the channel switch is called a connection event. Even when "
"no application data is transmitted or received, the two devices still "
"exchange link-layer data to maintain the connection. The connection interval "
"is the time interval between two connection events. It is measured in units "
"of 1.25ms, with a value range of 6 (7.5ms) to 3200 (4s)."

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:33
#: efe07011c54349dba4132a47319ecec1
msgid ""
"从机延时——这个参数的设置可以使从机跳过若干连接事件，这给了从机更多的灵活度，"
"如果它没有数据发送时，可以选择跳过连接时间继续休眠，以节省功耗。"
msgstr ""
"Slave latency — This parameter allows the slave device to skip several "
"connection events, giving the slave more flexibility. If it has no data to "
"send, it can skip the connection event and continue sleeping to reduce power "
"consumption."

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:34
#: e1b4a72e5ed240ceb21963399cf63198
msgid "管理超时——这是两个成功连接事件之间的最大允许的间隔，如果超过了这个时间"
msgstr ""
"Supervision timeout — This is the maximum allowed interval between two "
"successful connection events. If this time is exceeded"

#: ../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:35
#: ac0e1dace1a64bf8a510853e9e61c1c4
msgid ""
"（这个值的单位是 10ms）而没有成功的连接事件，设备被认为丢失连接，返回到未 连"
"接状态，管理超时的范围是 100（100ms）~3200（32s）另外，超时值必须大于有效的连"
"接间隔[有效的连接间隔=连接间隔*（1+从机延时）]。 - 安全管理——只有已认证的连接"
"中，特定的数据数据才能被读写，一旦连接建立，两个设备进行配对，当配对完成后，"
"形成加密连接的密钥，在典型的应用中，外设请求集中器提供密钥来完成配对工作。密"
"钥是一个固定的值，如 000000，也可以随机生成一个数据提供给使用者，当主机设备发"
"送正确的密钥后，两设备交换安全密钥并加密认证链接。在许多情况下，同一对外设和"
"主机会不时的连接和断开，ble 的安全机制中有一项特性，允许两个设备之间建立长久"
"的安全密钥信息，这种特性称为绑定，他允许两设备连接时快速的完成加密认证，而不"
"需要每次连接时执行配对的完整过程。"
msgstr ""
"(the unit of this value is 10ms) and no successful connection event occurs, "
"the device is considered to have lost the connection and returns to the "
"disconnected state. The supervision timeout range is 100 (100ms) to 3200 "
"(32s). In addition, the timeout value must be greater than the effective "
"connection interval [effective connection interval = connection interval × "
"(1 + slave latency)]. - Security management — Only in authenticated "
"connections can specific data be read and written. Once a connection is "
"established, the two devices perform pairing. After pairing is completed, a "
"key for the encrypted connection is generated. In typical applications, the "
"peripheral requests the central device to provide a key to complete the "
"pairing process. The key may be a fixed value, such as 000000, or a randomly "
"generated number provided to the user. When the central device sends the "
"correct key, the two devices exchange security keys and encrypt the "
"authenticated link. In many cases, the same pair of peripheral and central "
"devices may connect and disconnect from time to time. The BLE security "
"mechanism includes a feature that allows two devices to establish long-term "
"security key information. This feature is called bonding. It allows the two "
"devices to quickly complete encryption and authentication when reconnecting, "
"without having to perform the full pairing process every time."

